      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presented is a museum-quality 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This example retains its original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary powerplant, currently exhibiting factory-spec compression and a seamless transition between primary and secondary boost phases. The five-speed manual gearbox offers precise gate selection with zero synchro drag, feeding power through a perfectly calibrated Torsen limited-slip differential. The lightweight chassis remains free of fatigue, preserving the 50/50 weight distribution and torsional rigidity that define the FD\u2019s handling characteristics. Featuring an untouched double-wishbone suspension and pristine underbody components, this vehicle provides the unfiltered, tactile feedback expected of a showroom-fresh apex car. An investment-grade specimen for the discerning collector.",
